{"id": "1517265613561794721", "channel_id": "1517265613561794721", "type": 0, "author_id": "640213495815733298", "author_name": "eternall_dog", "author_bot": false, "content": "Hello,\n\nI am a web developer and a huge fan of Morimens. I would like to create a free community resource focused entirely on the game's PvP content (Traphase).\n\nMy goal is to build a tracker website where players can search by their player ID to view their match history, calculate personal win rates, and analyze the current meta (such as top player builds and popular deck archetypes).\n\nI would like to know if there is an official public API available for third-party developers, or if there are any plans to release one in the near future.\n\nAlternatively, if a public API is not available, would it be permissible to develop a lightweight desktop log-parser for users to track their local match data? I want to ensure my approach aligns perfectly with your terms of service.\n\nThank you for your time and for creating such an amazing game! I look forward to your reply.", "timestamp": "2026-06-18T20:31:51.705000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [{"emoji": "🔥", "emoji_id": null, "count": 5}], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": "1517265613561794721", "flags": 0, "thread_title": "Inquiry regarding API access / Community PvP Tracker for Morimens", "forum_channel_id": "1180845276823564288", "thread_tags": ["1361169005435420785"], "is_thread_starter": true}
{"id": "1517258278961152137", "channel_id": "1517258278961152137", "type": 0, "author_id": "1424954154656464936", "author_name": "oatstemp", "author_bot": false, "content": "1. The points system needs to be adjusted.\nLosing feels bad. Really bad \nLosing is normal. If I lose to someone way lower than me, feel free to rip out a chunk of my points.\nBut I don't think it is reasonable to lose a 140+ points to someone within or slightly above my range. \n\n\n2.  We need a mode where we can test team comps.\n It should be as customizable as possible. At the very least, we should  be able to make a full team, equip them with wheels etc. Maybe even customize the enemy team. You can take it a step further and allow us to swap teams in order to simulate a real match. The current system of using one character is very lacking. \n\n3.  We need a mode that doesn't have points attached to it.\nIn the current system, your points are tied to the rewards you receive every week, and those rewards are very precious. If you remember my first point, losing costs a lot of points. What happens when you reach 'Legendary' rank in one mode? The incentive to keep playing that mode decreases if you care about the rewards you receive. I have stopped playing All Pick because I don't want to risk plummeting down the leaderboards and thus forfeiting the subsequent rewards.\n\nAdding a points free mode lets people experiment, have fun and goof around as much as possible. \n\n4. Pay more attention to the meta\nAt times, some team comps are so strong that using any other thing is practically offering the enemy free ELO.", "timestamp": "2026-06-18T20:02:43+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [{"emoji": "🔥", "emoji_id": null, "count": 3}], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": "1517258278961152137", "flags": 0, "thread_title": "My suggestions for Improving Traphase.", "forum_channel_id": "1180845276823564288", "thread_tags": ["1361168939622727801"], "is_thread_starter": true}
