{"id": "1517244861126938675", "channel_id": "1515634790076907610", "type": 0, "author_id": "99950645313798144", "author_name": "zyocuh", "author_bot": false, "content": "I did want to add a bit more perspective on \"people wouldnt need them if they were increased\" \n\nI have been playing for 486 days, purchaced probably more than half the battle passes and on only 5 teams for D-Tide I have 7 units who dont have maxed skills. So 7 out of 20 units still without maxed skills and I am also currently out of materials.\n\nAnother perspective is \n\nMaxed Skilled units 6/6/6/6/6/6: 18\nUnmaxed Skills: 38\n\nApprox 16 months, paying for BP and only 18 maxed units. I could probably shuffle things around and get that higher but having less investment in some units who have some skills at 5 reduce them to 3 and get others to 6. Lets say 25 maxed unit and 31 unmaxed. But is there a REASON we cant have units with max skills? There are so many units now, what is the harm of having every unit at max for a player whose given over a year of their life to the game?", "timestamp": "2026-06-18T19:09:23.939000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": "1515634790076907610", "flags": 0, "thread_title": "Can we increase Arcane Dominion runs?", "forum_channel_id": "1180845276823564288", "thread_tags": ["1361168939622727801"]}
{"id": "1517245150219206729", "channel_id": "1515634790076907610", "type": 0, "author_id": "99950645313798144", "author_name": "zyocuh", "author_bot": false, "content": "Even if they just doubled them, in 16 months you STILL wouldnt max out every unit in the game", "timestamp": "2026-06-18T19:10:32.864000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": "1515634790076907610", "flags": 0, "thread_title": "Can we increase Arcane Dominion runs?", "forum_channel_id": "1180845276823564288", "thread_tags": ["1361168939622727801"]}
